heavy equipment transport system (abbreviated as hets) is a term applied (primarily) to a u.s. army logistics vehicle transport system, the primary purpose of which is to transport the m1 abrams tank. it is also used to transport, deploy, and evacuate armored personnel carriers, self-propelled artillery, armored bulldozers and other heavy vehicles and equipment of all types. the current u.s. army vehicle used in this role is an oshkosh-built m1070 tractor unit which is coupled to a drs technologies m1000 semi-trailer. this combination replaced the earlier oshkosh-built m911 tractor unit and m747 semi-trailer.